[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a double-free detected by AddressSanitizer when running the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer-based “api” harness against libxml2. The sanitizer report shows that a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmall memory block [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m11[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m allocated via xmlFuzzMalloc/xmlStrdup/xmlNewComment [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis freed twice inside `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `fuzz/api.c`.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt removed the existing `xmlFreeNodeList` function and inserted a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnew `xmlNodeGetContent` definition in its place. After applying the patch, the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuild fails with errors such as “function definition is not allowed here” at the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnew `xmlNodeGetContent` declaration, followed by numerous “use of undeclared [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentifier ‘cur’[0m[35m/[0m[39m‘next’[0m[35m/[0m[39m‘parent’” errors in the remaining code.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzing run on `api` triggers an AddressSanitizer error:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - “ERROR: AddressSanitizer: attempting double-free on [0m[1;36m0x5020000000b0[0m[39m”[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - The first free occurs in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz/api.[0m[1;92mc:3580:9[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecond free immediately follows at the same location.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - The [0m[1;36m11[0m[39m-byte region was originally allocated via `malloc` in `xmlFuzzMalloc` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ `xmlStrndup` → `xmlNewComment` in `tree.[0m[1;92mc:2583:17[0m[39m`.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack traces involve:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mapi.[0m[1;92mc:3580[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `fuzzer::ExecuteCallback` → `RunOneTest` → `FuzzerDriver` → `main`  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch deletes the entire `xmlFreeNodeList` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginally lines [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m~[0m[1;36m3510[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3569[0m[39m in `tree.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Immediately after the closing brace of a preceding function, it adds a new [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     xmlChar *[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mxmlNodeGetContent[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlNode *cur[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* many switch cases returning xmlStrdup/xmlNodeListGetString *[0m[35m/[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No adjustments are made to surrounding braces or function boundaries.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Resulting Errors  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The compiler reports at `tree.[0m[1;92mc:3573:39[0m[39m`:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     “error: function definition is not allowed here”  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This indicates that the new `xmlNodeGetContent` was placed inside another [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction’s body.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Subsequent errors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m3622[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3644[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m all complain that `cur`, `next`, `parent`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39metc., are undeclared:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `next = cur->next;`  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `parent = cur->parent;`  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type == XML_DOCUMENT_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The cascade of errors suggests that the removal of `xmlFreeNodeList` shifted [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode, causing mismatched braces and orphaned references in the rest of the file.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Code Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `tree.c`:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The original `xmlFreeNodeList` implementation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m3510[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3569[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The insertion point for `xmlNodeGetContent`—brace alignment and function [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscope.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • References to `next`, `parent`, and `cur` in the remainder of the file [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mensure they are inside valid functions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz/api.c` around line [0m[1;36m3580[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The code path that frees the same buffer twice.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Interactions between `xmlNewComment`, `xmlStrdup`, and any cleanup routines.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In string utility functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlstring.c`, `fuzz/fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Allocation via `xmlFuzzMalloc` and `xmlStrdup` that ultimately produce the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble-free symptom.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo cause speculation or fixes are provided here; this report is focused on [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msummarizing the failure, the patch attempt, and pointing out the affected code [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregions.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1683[0m[39m:            tmp->parent = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlNodePtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m cur;[0m                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1685[0m[39m:                cur->last = tmp;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Revert the erroneous removal of xmlFreeNodeList and the misplaced insertion of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeGetContent:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Restore the original xmlFreeNodeList implementation in tree.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m~[0m[1;36m3577[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3662[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exactly as it was in the initial codebase. This preserves the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtree‐freeing logic and correct brace alignment.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove the misplaced xmlNodeGetContent definition that was inserted inside [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlFreeNodeList; ensure that no function definitions are nested and that all braces[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatch their intended functions.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Locate the existing xmlNodeGetContent implementation in tree.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround where [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeListGetString and related utilities are defined[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. It typically looks like:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     xmlChar *[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mxmlNodeGetContent[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlNode *cur[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         xmlChar *ret = NULL;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         switch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Element/document, text, CDATA, PI, entity refs handled here *[0m[35m/[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             case XML_COMMENT_NODE:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mBAD_CAST [0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m <-- problematic[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[39m* other cases[0m[33m...[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* fallback: raw string *[0m[35m/[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             ret = [0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->doc, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlNodePtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mcur, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mret[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Modify the XML_COMMENT_NODE branch so it always returns a newly allocated [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mduplicate[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m string:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change `[0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` to `[0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures that callers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., the fuzzer harness via xmlNodeGetContent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreceive their own copy to free, while xmlFreeNodeList continues to free the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal `cur->content` when it frees the node.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify that all other branches in xmlNodeGetContent already produce fresh [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocations:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Element/document nodes use `[0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetString[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which allocates.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - TEXT, CDATA, PI nodes already `[0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ENTITY_REF_NODE uses `[0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetString[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The default/fallback uses `[0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which duplicates [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternals.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Build and run the libFuzzer “api” harness:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The double‐free should no longer occur because the buffer returned by [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeGetContent is decoupled from the node’s internal content. The harness free [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m frees only the duplicate; xmlFreeNodeList frees the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnode’s internal content exactly once.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The root cause is that xmlNodeGetContent returned raw `cur->content` for comment [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnodes, leading to a double‐free when the harness freed that pointer and [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlFreeNodeList later freed it again.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By ensuring xmlNodeGetContent always returns a duplicate, we eliminate [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverlapping ownership and preserve the cleanup semantics of xmlFreeNodeList.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- We avoid touching any harness or fuzzing logic; only the tree.c source is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodified.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The rest of the codebase logic and tests remain unchanged, so existing [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality is preserved.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPotential Side Effects and Mitigations:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Callers that assumed `[0m[1;35mxmlNodeGetContent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` might return an internal pointer must [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow handle the duplicated memory and free it [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich the harness already does[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. No [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode in libxml2 relies on pointer identity here.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The additional duplication for comment nodes has negligible performance/memory [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimpact given the typical usage patterns.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All other node types behave as before.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRelevant Code Ranges Updated:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>tree.c: [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlFreeNodeList restoration: ~[0m[1;36m3577[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3662[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>tree.c: [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlNodeGetContent modification: locate XML_COMMENT_NODE [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcase[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibxml2[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp7x1k5z8x[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce api[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer–detected double-free in libxml2’s tree [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling code when running the `api` fuzz target. The crash occurs in [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` and is traced to freeing the same memory region twice in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tree.c`.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was attempted that inserts a `case XML_COMMENT_NODE` branch to always [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstrdup comments and restructures the node-freeing loop around line [0m[1;36m3580[0m[39m in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tree.c`. After applying the patch, compilation fails with multiple errors such as [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“`case` statement not in switch,” undeclared identifiers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`cur`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, extraneous [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbraces, and improper function/parameter syntax.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Running `out/api` under AddressSanitizer with a single test case [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggers a double-free.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer log shows `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` called twice on the same pointer at [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/libxml2/fuzz/[0m[95mapi.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m3580:9[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation happened via `xmlFuzzMalloc` → `xmlStrdup` → `xmlNewComment`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The second free occurs later in the node-cleanup routine in `tree.c`, indicating [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomment nodes are freed both at creation and during recursive cleanup.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The failure stack points to `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` calling into the tree [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mutilities, specifically the cleanup code handling various node types.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Comment nodes appear to share a buffer freed elsewhere, leading to the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble-free.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash reproducibly happens in the recursive node-deletion function starting [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround line [0m[1;36m3580[0m[39m in `tree.c`.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modifications around line [0m[1;36m1525[0m[39m in `tree.c` to treat `XML_COMMENT_NODE` as a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecial case: returning a fresh `[0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` earlier.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Extensive reindentation and restructuring of the `xmlFreeNodeList`-style loop [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnear lines [0m[1;36m3588[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3615[0m[39m to unify freeing logic, including moving `[0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` inside[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe loop and updating brace levels.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch replaces some `if`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`else` blocks, adds `case XML_COMMENT_NODE`, and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanges spacing/indentation.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Application Result  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compiler errors at the new `case XML_COMMENT_NODE:` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot inside a `switch`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- References to `cur` undeclared in the context of the inserted code at line [0m[1;36m1528[0m[39m. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Misplaced braces leading to “extraneous closing brace” errors around lines [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3668[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3681[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Warnings about missing type specifiers and invalid parameter lists at the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minjected `[0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` line.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Overall, the patch does not cleanly integrate: control structures are malformed, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscoping is wrong, and the free loop’s bounds/braces are mismatched.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The implementation of the recursive node-deletion function in `tree.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m3570[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3620[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand how comment-node content is freed.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The handling of `xmlNewComment`, `xmlStrdup`, and how their buffers are tracked [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand later freed.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Ensure proper ownership transfer of the strdup’ed buffers for comment nodes [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mversus other node types.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Examine the switch or conditional that should surround `case XML_COMMENT_NODE` to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocate the correct hook point.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3622[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type == XML_XINCLUDE_START[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3623[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type == XML_XINCLUDE_END[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3624[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->properties != NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3625[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mxmlFreePropList[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->properties[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3626[0m[39m:   [0m[39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type != XML_ELEMENT_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3627[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type != XML_XINCLUDE_START[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3628[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type != XML_XINCLUDE_END[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3629[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type != XML_ENTITY_REF_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3630[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content != [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlChar *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->properties[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3631[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mDICT_FREE[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3632[0m[39m:   [0m[39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3633[0m[39m:   [0m[39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type == XML_ELEMENT_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3634[0m[39m:   [0m[39m         [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type == XML_XINCLUDE_START[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3635[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type == XML_XINCLUDE_END[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3636[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->nsDef != NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3637[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mxmlFreeNsList[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->nsDef[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3638[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3639[0m[39m:   [0m[39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3640[0m[39m:   [0m[39m     * When a node is a text node or a comment, it uses a global static[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3641[0m[39m:   [0m[39m     * variable for the name of the node.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3642[0m[39m:   [0m[39m     * Otherwise the node name might come from the document's[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3643[0m[39m:   [0m[39m     * dictionary[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3644[0m[39m:   [0m[39m     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3645[0m[39m:   [0m[39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->name != NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3646[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type != XML_TEXT_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m &&[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3647[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type != XML_COMMENT_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3648[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mDICT_FREE[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->name[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3649[0m[39m:   [0m[39m    [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3650[0m[39m:   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz/api.[0m[1;92mc:3579[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m3587[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3579[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < REG_MAX; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3580[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3581[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3582[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < REG_MAX; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3583[0m[39m:        xmlNodePtr node = vars->nodes[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3584[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3585[0m[39m:        vars->nodes[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = NULL;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3586[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mdropNode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3587[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Identify the root cause and high-level plan  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The double-free happens because the fuzzer harness stores pointers from two [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msources:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – vars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m which holds pointers returned by the API under test [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeGetContent for comment nodes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – vars->nodes[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m which holds xmlNodePtr’s whose →content buffer is the same [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   At teardown, the harness calls [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m first [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfreeing that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then calls [0m[1;35mdropNode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → xmlFreeNodeList → [0m[1;35mDICT_FREE[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mfreeing the same buffer again[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The correct remedy is to break the aliasing between the string returned to the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplication and the internal buffer of the comment node. We must modify the public [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPI [0m[1;39m([0m[39min tree.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so that when the user asks for a comment node’s content, the API [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns a freshly allocated copy – leaving the node’s internal buffer solely owned [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby the node deletion routines.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Locate and patch the appropriate getter function  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In tree.c, the function xmlNodeGetContent [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand its HTML alias xmlNodeGetContent[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhas a switch/if-chain over node types. Currently, it returns node->content directly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor comment nodes. We will insert a case for XML_COMMENT_NODE that does:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – if cur->content is NULL, return [0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mBAD_CAST [0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – else return [0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   and fall through in all other cases to the existing logic. This ensures [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m receives its own copy.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preserve existing logic and formatting  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Identify the exact switch or if-chain in xmlNodeGetContent [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1520[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min tree.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Introduce a proper `case XML_COMMENT_NODE:` inside the switch statement on [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnode->type.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Do not alter any braces or indentation outside this minimal change.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Do not touch xmlFreeNodeList or the harness. The node destructor will continue[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto free comment buffers exactly once.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Implementation steps  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In tree.c locate xmlNodeGetContent [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor xmlGetNodeContent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m function.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Inside the [0m[1;35mswitch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->type[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m add immediately after the XML_TEXT_NODE [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbranch:[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        case XML_COMMENT_NODE:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m* comment nodes internal buffer must not be returned directly *[0m[35m/[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->content == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mBAD_CAST [0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Leave all other branches untouched.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Ensure xmlStrdup is available [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit is the existing duplication function used [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby xmlNewComment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Recompile and verify that:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        – The compiler sees `case` inside the switch – no “case not in switch” [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        – No undefined identifiers – use `node` or `cur` consistently with [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msurrounding code.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Run the fuzz target. The harness’s [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m now frees the copy,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand xmlFreeNodeList’s DICT_FREE frees only the node’s own content buffer.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Verification and side-effect analysis  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Existing APIs for element nodes, text nodes, etc., are unaffected.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The only change is for comment nodes: callers now get a duplicated buffer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrather than the internal pointer. This is safe: before, callers were not documented[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto own the internal pointer. Returning a fresh copy is semantically correct.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No memory leak: the new allocation is freed by the harness. The node’s [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal buffer is freed by xmlFreeNodeList.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No change to harness, no breaking of other tests.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Reference to similar solution  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Libxml2 already duplicates attribute and CDATA values in certain getters. [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAligning comment-node handling with that established pattern ensures consistency.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
